n for existential self-understanding.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 0aSociologyxPhilosophy. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh  aAnarchy.  aDeconstruction.  aDemocracy.  aExistence.  aImpolitical.  aInfrapolitics.  aOntotheology.  aPosthegemony.  aTrue Life.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073909140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823298389zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823298389423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823298389/original  a978-3-11-073909-1  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK